column14: ADJUSTED MGH FOR 2ND DWL ERROR (-0.004M) Rip rap on LB made for low 0.8 velocities, measured 0.2/0.6/0.8 where needed. Sand bar around tagmark 14m. Swapped to 50lb weight and meter on 30lb hole for right half of channel where depths/velocities are lower. Used coeficients 0.98, 0.99 for depth corrections as needed. Inserted one panel in fast flow with 50lb weight- 75 was definitely better. HFC Comments: Control Condition: Clear Measurement Section Condition: Open Weather Condition: Sunny Wind Velocity: 5 Wind Direction: U/S Built a rock stilling well for cut, still a lot of surge. Have used BM 9 since stn rebuild since BM 7 was not accessible for the most part, but BM 7 is likely more stable (BM 7 is less likely to have risen 0.007m than BM 9 dropped that amount). Rearranged levels to take DWL from BM 7. Will need to edit levels since Fall 2020. Reset HG to 2.010m at 11:13pst. Mid-section
